					<description><![CDATA[I tend to use &quot;Yours Sincerely&quot; for most correspondence. Work emails especially, I&#039;ll sign off &quot;thank you,&quot;. There&#039;s just something about &quot;Yours Sincerely&quot; that feel right for most of the letters I write. If they&#039;re family, a friend, or something along those lines, probably not. &quot;Yours Faithfully&quot; always sounds odd to me. Not sure why.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I tend to use &#8220;Yours Sincerely&#8221; for most correspondence. Work emails especially, I&#8217;ll sign off &#8220;thank you,&#8221;. There&#8217;s just something about &#8220;Yours Sincerely&#8221; that feel right for most of the letters I write. If they&#8217;re family, a friend, or something along those lines, probably not. &#8220;Yours Faithfully&#8221; always sounds odd to me. Not sure why.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
